# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ** DEVELOPMENT SIGNING KEY — NOT FOR PRODUCTION USE **
#
# This is an MCUboot image-signing private key (ECDSA P-256, PKCS#8 PEM),
# generated for the UWB tag firmware bench/CI build only:
#
#   openssl genpkey -algorithm EC -pkeyopt ec_paramgen_curve:P-256 \
#     -out keys/mcuboot_dev_key.pem
#
# It is intentionally committed to source control so that `west build
# --sysbuild` produces a reproducible signed image for every developer and
# CI runner without an out-of-band key-distribution step (ADR-0040 #6:
# "Use a development signing key committed for the build (documented as
# non-production)").
#
# MCUboot embeds the corresponding *public* key into the bootloader image at
# build time (sysbuild derives it automatically from this file via
# SB_CONFIG_BOOT_SIGNATURE_KEY_FILE in sysbuild.conf) and rejects any
# application image not signed with the matching private key.
#
# DO NOT use this key to sign a production/field release. Before shipping
# tags outside the bench:
#   1. Generate a new key with restricted custody (HSM / secrets manager,
#      not a git repo) — see ADR-0040 "Signing — dev baseline now, hardened
#      later" and the deferred production-key-management / secure-boot
#      hardening work (CONFIG_MCUBOOT_HW_KEY / KMU, image encryption,
#      anti-rollback counters).
#   2. Re-flash all bench/CI devices' MCUboot with the new public key before
#      retiring this one, or they will refuse the new signed images.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
